rComments: Super good prof, would take him again. Assignments/project were very easy and corrected within 1-2 days with good feedback. Responds very quickly to emails. Really nice and caring! Interesting content too

I loved this course and would take another class with this prof! As long as you do your readings and properly study for your tests and exams, you will pass, maybe not with flying colors, but you will pass! Bonus points: everything we learned was extremely interesting and the prof truly is passionate about what he teaches,
I really don't like history, but I loved this class!

Si vous suivez ses guides d'examen (il envoit un guide à la classe pour nous dire quoi étudier pour chaque exams) à la perfection, vous allez passer son cours avec brio. Ses examens ne sont pas cumulatif. Il ne demande pas que vous recrachez toutes les notes du cours par coeur pour réussir (mais faites le si vous voullez 100%).
He was my favourite professor. He is very passionate about what he teaches and does his best to make sure you get good grades and understand the material.
amazing prof!! interesting class, he know very well what he's talking about. I was very lucky to have this prof for 4 classes!

Un des meilleurs cours de mon Bac. Super intéressant! Il connait son sujet, est drôle, excellent pédagogue. Je conseil le cours à tous. Les critères d'évaluation et les attentes pour les examens sont claires. Merci Prof Renaud!

Fun course, passionate prof. He's fully into archaeology, even put together a 35% mini-dig for the class to do in groups which was super fun. Gives out outlines for midterms and finals, and his notes are online and clear-cut. Take extra notes in class and show up, you'll do fine. Have had him twice and would take another class with him again.

Great prof, easy grader. Best part of the class was the online portion, he posts EVERYTHING which is phenomenal. Very quick at answering emails and questions. His test outlines are word for word the test, take my word for it.

I had Prof Renaud for CLA1501 and he was a great!  Only one writing assignment all semester long, clear course outline, responds to emails quickly and gave great lectures. All 3 exams were very fair and he gave great outlines for them ahead of time, making studying very easy.  Overall great prof! I would hope to have him again in the future.
Connais la matiere, passionné mais tres mauvaise gestion du temps. Decu par la fin.

Extremely helpful prof. From the first day, you could tell he was extremely into what he taught, and wanted you to do well. Gave you extensive study notes for all tests and exams. I highly recommend having him as a prof for any course.

Un cours facile mais intéressant. Je n'ai pas ouvert le livre. Il est très gentil, un peu redondant mais comique et compréhensif. Il connait très bien sa matière! Toutesfois, son cours est surtout axé sur l'art...

Quirky funny. Way too concentrated on the arts, but it doesnt matter as he grades very easy. Go see him if there is a problem, there won't be anymore. Interesting; I got much higher then I should've/deserved.

Very nice prof, tells jokes that are so lame, they're funny. All in all, easy to follow but spends a bit too much time on art as opposed to actual history. Good prof overall if you're interested in ancient Greece.
He's really nice and funny. However, his class is all about art (like learning 100 different types of pottery).
Awesome Teacher!!! Interresting! His exam's have alot of material. But over all, he's a good teacher. I am happy that i finally got a teacher that his specialty is what he's teaching.
Good teacher, nice and clear. He spent too music time on art though and not enough on history.

Awesome prof, all the notes are on the net, really clear about the expectations, two tests, one exam, and 30% of easy participation goes to ur final grade, no doubt a very good teacher and an easy and fun class to have
Very easy grader "you wrote this but I think you meant this so I gave it to you". Classes get a little long though. He loves the subject and has interesting stories.
No Comments
Organised notes but haphasard teaching style. Easy marker who is really passionate about what he teaches. NOt fantastic but you could do a lot worse.
